Macquarie disclosed BHP Billiton PLC (LON:BLT), boosting its price target to 1,450.00GBX earlier today


By Al Wild


Updated: July 19, 2017




Stating a potential upside of 0.12%, Macquarie raised the target price of BHP Billiton PLC (LON:BLT) to 1,450.00GBX 
Previously on 7/19/2017, Liberum Capital reported about BHP Billiton PLC (LON:BLT) held steady the target price at 800.00GBX.  At the time, this indicated a possible downside of -0.39%.
Yesterday BHP Billiton PLC (LON:BLT) traded 0.53% higher at 1,290.00GBX.  The company’s 50-day moving average is 1,207.87GBX and its 200-day moving average is 1,276.45GBX.  The last stock close price is up 3.37% from the 200-day moving average, compared to the S&P 500 which has increased 0.07% over the same time.  6,263,110 shares of BLT traded hands, down from an average trading volume of 8,212,660 
Recent Performance Chart

BHP Billiton PLC has 52 week low of 903.40GBX and a 52 week high of 1,518.50GBX with a PE ratio of 28.32  and has a market capitalization of 0 GBX.
In addition to Macquarie reporting its stock price target, a total of 23 brokerages have issued a ratings update on the company.  The average stock price target is 11.79GBX with 3 brokerages rating the stock a strong buy, 4 brokerages rating the stock a buy, 16 brokerages rating the stock a hold, 2 brokerages rating the stock a underperform, and finally 1 brokerage rating the stock a sell.
Brief Synopsis On BHP Billiton PLC (LON:BLT)
BHP Billiton Plc is a global resources company. The Company is a producer of various commodities, including iron ore, metallurgical coal, copper and uranium. Its segments include Petroleum, Copper, Iron Ore and Coal. The Petroleum segment is engaged in the exploration, development and production of oil and gas. The Copper segment is engaged in mining of copper, silver, lead, zinc, molybdenum, uranium and gold. The Iron Ore segment is engaged in mining of iron ore. The Coal segment is engaged in mining of metallurgical coal and thermal (energy) coal. Its businesses include Minerals Australia, Minerals Americas, Petroleum and Marketing. It extracts and processes minerals, oil and gas from its production operations located primarily in Australia and the Americas. It manages product distribution through its global logistics chain, including freight and pipeline transportation. It sells its products through direct supply agreements with its customers and on global commodity exchanges.

