BHP Billiton PLC (LON:BLT) Gets GBX 1350.00 Target By Citigroup, Eyegate Pharmaceuticals (EYEG) SI Decreased By 8.45%


					
						July 20, 2017 - By wolcottdaily

 Eyegate Pharmaceuticals Incorporated (NASDAQ:EYEG) had a decrease of 8.45% in short interest. EYEG’s SI was 626,500 shares in July as released by FINRA. Its down 8.45% from 684,300 shares previously. With 268,600 avg volume, 2 days are for Eyegate Pharmaceuticals Incorporated (NASDAQ:EYEG)’s short sellers to cover EYEG’s short positions. The SI to Eyegate Pharmaceuticals Incorporated’s float is 10.08%. The stock increased 0.76% or $0.01 on July 19, reaching $1.32. About shares traded. Eyegate Pharmaceuticals Inc (NASDAQ:EYEG) has declined 40.33% since July 20, 2016 and is downtrending. It has underperformed by 57.03% the S&P500.







 BHP Billiton PLC (LON:BLT) was downgraded by Citigroup to a Neutral rating in a analysts note revealed to investors on Thursday, 20 July. The firm now has GBX 1350.00 PT on the stock.
Among 2 analysts covering Eyegate Pharmaceuticals (NASDAQ:EYEG), 2 have Buy rating, 0 Sell and 0 Hold. Therefore 100% are positive. Eyegate Pharmaceuticals had 2 analyst reports since November 12, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. The firm has “Buy” rating given on Thursday, November 12 by Maxim Group. The stock has “Buy” rating by Chardan Capital Markets on Wednesday, December 23.
Eyegate Pharmaceuticals, Inc. is a clinical-stage specialty pharmaceutical company. The company has market cap of $14.22 million. The Firm is focused on developing and commercializing therapeutics and drug delivery systems for treating diseases of the eye. It currently has negative earnings. The Company’s lead product, EGP-437, incorporates a reformulated topically active corticosteroid, dexamethasone phosphate, which is delivered into the ocular tissues through its drug delivery system, the EyeGate II Delivery System.
 About 1.62M shares traded. BHP Billiton plc (LON:BLT) has 0.00% since July 20, 2016 and is . It has underperformed by 16.70% the S&P500.
Among 31 analysts covering BHP Billiton PLC (LON:BLT), 9 have Buy rating, 6 Sell and 16 Hold. Therefore 29% are positive. BHP Billiton PLC has GBX 1850 highest and GBX 515 lowest target. GBX 1145.46’s average target is -12.99% below currents GBX 1316.5 stock price. BHP Billiton PLC had 435 analyst reports since July 22, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. The firm earned “Hold” rating on Wednesday, July 20 by Canaccord Genuity. On Tuesday, September 15 the stock rating was maintained by Goldman Sachs with “Neutral”. The firm has “Sell” rating given on Tuesday, April 25 by Goldman Sachs. The stock has “Buy” rating by Jefferies on Monday, November 9. The stock of BHP Billiton plc (LON:BLT) has “Hold” rating given on Friday, July 22 by Investec. The firm has “Sector Perform” rating by RBC Capital Markets given on Tuesday, February 9. The firm earned “Hold” rating on Monday, September 14 by Deutsche Bank. The rating was maintained by Deutsche Bank with “Hold” on Wednesday, July 13. BNP Paribas maintained it with “Neutral” rating and GBX 1268 target in Thursday, December 1 report. The rating was maintained by JP Morgan with “Underweight” on Monday, November 7.
BHP Billiton Plc is a global resources company. The company has market cap of 76.22 billion GBP. The Firm is a producer of various commodities, including iron ore, metallurgical coal, copper and uranium. It has a 36.78 P/E ratio. The Company’s divisions include Petroleum, Copper, Iron Ore and Coal.








